Daddy, I'm putting my foot down.

17:48.270 --> 17:49.270
You got to tell Mom.

17:49.316 --> 17:50.364
It's the right thing to do

17:50.458 --> 17:51.978
and I'm not leaving till you tell her.

17:52.170 --> 17:53.731
I just told her.

17:53.910 --> 17:56.215
She's crying in the kitchen.

18:10.389 --> 18:12.621
Oh! Cynthia?!

18:14.637 --> 18:16.728
I'm ready to talk now, Joe.

18:17.028 --> 18:21.520
Okay, 'cause I thought for a
minute you were gonna kill me.

18:24.342 --> 18:25.801
Good.

18:26.520 --> 18:28.801
Think that.

18:29.246 --> 18:32.020
You've made me that woman, Joe,

18:32.530 --> 18:36.129
that woman that everybody
pities and whispers about

18:36.231 --> 18:39.551
when she walks
through the grocery store.

18:40.012 --> 18:42.121
I don't know how to be that woman.

18:42.450 --> 18:46.449
I'm always the woman
who's doing the whispering.

18:47.545 --> 18:49.785
Cynthia, I am so sorry.

18:49.989 --> 18:54.137
And... anything you need,
you just tell me.

19:02.871 --> 19:04.598
What's his name?

19:05.246 --> 19:07.145
Morris.

19:08.794 --> 19:11.723
That's a terrible name.

19:31.928 --> 19:33.928
What do you think Mom
and Dad got to tell us?

19:34.150 --> 19:36.436
I'm worried that they're
getting a divorce.

19:36.756 --> 19:39.917
This is a bad-news restaurant.

19:40.115 --> 19:41.797
Well, my parents told me
they were getting divorced

19:41.821 --> 19:43.880
at TGI Fridays 'cause they
knew no one would notice

19:43.959 --> 19:45.326
if I made a scene.

19:45.724 --> 19:46.771
Did you?

19:46.873 --> 19:49.030
Oh, big time.

19:49.308 --> 19:50.449
Hey, kids.

19:50.558 --> 19:51.631
- Hey, Mom and Dad.
- Oh, there...

19:51.655 --> 19:52.904
there they are, looking good.

19:52.929 --> 19:54.044
Mom and Dad. Lovebirds.

19:54.069 --> 19:55.903
- Mom and...
- Knock it off.

20:00.320 --> 20:03.210
Listen, everybody,
we're gonna get through this.

20:03.413 --> 20:06.656
Just because your father
lied to me for 35 years,

20:06.681 --> 20:09.156
it does not make him a bad man.

20:09.363 --> 20:11.039
It makes him a flawed man

20:11.064 --> 20:14.219
who will probably have
difficulty getting into heaven,

20:14.326 --> 20:16.828
but that is not my burden to carry.

20:17.164 --> 20:19.050
Well, I'm gonna deal with
that when I get there.

20:19.124 --> 20:21.351
I can be very persuasive.

20:22.151 --> 20:24.638
So, how are we gonna handle this?

20:24.929 --> 20:26.703
Gonna joke about it?

20:26.867 --> 20:28.078
Sweep it under the rug?

20:28.171 --> 20:30.280
Just let me know, I don't have
strong feelings either way.

20:30.304 --> 20:34.250
No, we're gonna be
very honest, very open.

20:34.326 --> 20:37.187
I mean, all families
have things to deal with.

20:37.339 --> 20:42.445
You know, my husband
has a son that isn't mine.

20:42.648 --> 20:44.402
So, there it is.

20:44.566 --> 20:46.841
Know who you're sitting with.

20:47.254 --> 20:49.574
We love each other,
we're a strong family

20:49.647 --> 20:51.722
and we're gonna get through this.

20:52.152 --> 20:55.758
She slept with my brother
and we're still together.

20:58.004 --> 21:00.847
Okay. Well...

21:01.034 --> 21:03.183
let's eat.

